## Overview
The current repo violates the intended SDK boundary: `src/sdk/index.ts` imports and re-exports from `@/tools/video-editor/runtime/renderability.ts` and `@/tools/video-editor`, while the existing SDK import guard and smoke test can pass despite host leakage or missing TypeScript tooling.

The latest critique does not indicate that this plan targets the wrong subsystem or root cause. It flags a verification-quality issue in the final broad-gate criterion: baseline attribution was still written as a hard gate that depended on subjective judgment. The implementation approach remains unchanged: move portable contracts and identity-sensitive public values into canonical SDK-owned modules, update host code to consume those SDK bindings, then harden validation around the boundary.

Identity-sensitive public values cannot be mirrored. `TimelineVersionConflictError`, `isTimelineVersionConflictError`, `getStableConfigSignature`, and `BUILTIN_CLIP_TYPES` must have one canonical implementation after extraction. The SDK will own the canonical portable implementations, and host code will import those SDK-owned bindings so consumers see the same class/function/constant identities that the host uses.

This milestone remains a bridge toward the M4 North Star. `src/sdk/index.ts` may remain the public barrel for M0, but every export it serves must resolve through SDK-owned modules, and no file under `src/sdk/**` may resolve a static import, export-from, or literal dynamic import into `src/tools/video-editor/**`.

